<br>
&quot;An exploit is a situation that exists such that a player can take advantage of a bug or unintended design consequence to achieve an unfair advantage over other players, especially in terms of items, platinum, experience, or spawn competition. <br>
<br>
The major problem is that you defined exploit using equally undefined and judgemental words:<br>
Define what is fair or unfair.<br>
Define what is intended.<br>
<br>
The additional comments are all problematic:<br>
<br>
&quot;Also any situation that allows harassment of other players or the ability to make gains with zero risk would be an exploit.&quot;<br>
<br>
Gains at zero risk: I just made a mistletoe cutting sickle without leaving a combat-safe zone.<br>
<br>
Harassment is bad or wrong, but how did it enter into a discussion of exploits?  I'm not clear on that.<br>
<br>
&quot;More generally, the use of bugs and unintended features to generally break the foundations of the game and make it generally less fun.&quot;<br>
<br>
In such general terms, you can't expect this to be accepted as a logical definition which does not rely on opinion and individual interpretation.<br>
<br>
----<br>
<br>
Suppose there is a situation in game where you can do something in two different ways, and they work differently.  If one way works better, are you exploting if you do it that way?  Casting force shield after spiritual purity so they both stack would have been an exploit, then, by this definition?<br>
<br>
CoH is disabled in many zones, therefore using a rogue to drag a corpse to the raid is against what is intended for those zones, and this definition clearly labels that an exploit, but this is contrary to the opinion of verant and most players.<br>
<br>
Group buffs were explicitly changed to take hold on low level group members, but some people call it an exploit anyway.  Did verant intent change while the code base remained the same?  If so, this indicates that defining an exploit in rigid terms is impossible, and the &quot;case law&quot; definition holds true.<br>
<br>
